---
const rows = [
  {
    question: "What should I even test?",
    bench: "You figure it out (in TypeScript)",
    skillmaker: "Agents co-design evals with you, in plain English",
  },
  {
    question: "Is the tested thing the shipped thing?",
    bench: "You maintain a synced copy",
    skillmaker: "The skill itself is what runs — nothing to sync",
  },
  {
    question: "Which version earned this number?",
    bench: "Experiment names, if you're disciplined",
    skillmaker: "Pinned automatically: skill version + model",
  },
  {
    question: "It drifted — why?",
    bench: "Here's the score delta",
    skillmaker: "Here's the trail: what changed, and the research behind each choice",
  },
  {
    question: "Now fix it",
    bench: "Back to your editor",
    skillmaker: "The operating table is the same surface",
  },
];
---

<section id="vs-the-bench" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">
      vs. the eval bench
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-3xl">
      The score is the easy part.
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink-dim leading-relaxed">
      An eval platform tells you the score. It can&#39;t tell you what to
      test, which version earned the number, why it drifted, or how to fix
      it. That&#39;s the other 90% of the job.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface">
    <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-border font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-ink-dim">
          <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">The question you&#39;re actually asking</th>
          <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Eval bench</th>
          <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Skillmaker</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {
          rows.map((row) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-border last:border-b-0">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">{row.question}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-ink-dim">{row.bench}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-ink">{row.skillmaker}</td>
            </tr>
          ))
        }
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-dim">
      Instrumenting an API product with an eng team? Braintrust is genuinely
      good at that. But if you&#39;re on the hook for skills that ride
      inside agents, a bench in another tab is the schlep, not the
      solution.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
